SIMPLE: aliquot
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Aliquot
<hw>Al"i*quot</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>aliquot</ets> some, several; <ets>alius</ets> other +
<ets>quot</ets> how many: cf. F. <ets>aliquote</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Math.)</fld> <def>An <xex>aliquot</xex> part of a number or
quantity is one which will divide it without a remainder; <as>thus, 5 is
an <ex>aliquot</ex> part of 15</as>. Opposed to
<contr>aliquant</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Aliseptal</ent>⟦br⟧
